#<BLCMM v="1">
#<!!!You opened a file saved with BLCMM in FilterTool. Please update to BLCMM to properly open this file!!!>
<head>
    <type name="BL2" offline="false"/>
    <profiles>
        <profile name="default" current="true"/>
    </profiles>
</head>
<body>
    <category name="No Level Requirement For Gear (Focused)">
        <comment>Mod based on research of existing community work (OurLordAndSaviorGabeNewell / Nexus Mods #94).</comment>
        <comment></comment>
        <comment>This is a FOCUSED version covering the most commonly-used item categories.</comment>
        <comment>For complete coverage of every item in the game, use the full mod from Nexus.</comment>
        <comment></comment>
        <comment>What this does: sets bUsesPlayerLevelRequirement=False on item definitions</comment>
        <comment>so the game runtime doesn't block equipping high-level gear on low-level chars.</comment>
        <comment></comment>
        <comment>To use with our save editor: first patch your save to GameStage=80, then</comment>
        <comment>run this mod in-game so the level-80 weapon actually equips.</comment>
        <comment></comment>

        <category name="Artifacts">
            <comment>Covers all relic/artifact types from the base game + DLCs.</comment>
            <code profiles="default">set GD_Artifacts.A_Item.Artifact_AggressionA bUsesPlayerLevelRequirement False</code>
            <code profiles="default">set GD_Artifacts.A_Item.Artifact_AggressionB bUsesPlayerLevelRequirement False</code>
